WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.506 --> 00:00:11.541
[Rip]
<i>This'll be one of those days</i>

2
00:00:11.575 --> 00:00:13.127
that follow you to the grave.

3
00:00:13.196 --> 00:00:14.679
If either one of you
want to walk.

4
00:00:14.748 --> 00:00:16.334
- I won't hold it against you.
- We're with you.

5
00:00:16.403 --> 00:00:18.541
♪ dramatic. suspenseful music ♪

6
00:00:19.368 --> 00:00:21.472
- [Beth] How does this happen?
- [Rip] Foot-and-mouth.

7
00:00:21.541 --> 00:00:22.748
It's got to be the new bull.

8
00:00:22.851 --> 00:00:24.886
Cattle broker.
he fucked us. baby.

9
00:00:24.955 --> 00:00:27.610
<i>All the vet paperwork? Forged.</i>

10
00:00:29.782 --> 00:00:31.162
[bellowing]

11
00:00:31.231 --> 00:00:32.575
<i>I don't know how
we're gonna tell Carter.</i>

12
00:00:32.644 --> 00:00:35.024
You're the prettiest woman
I've ever seen.

13
00:00:35.093 --> 00:00:36.610
Carter has a pure heart.

14
00:00:36.713 --> 00:00:37.955
If you fuck with it.

15
00:00:38.024 --> 00:00:39.541
I will make your life
a living hell.

16
00:00:39.575 --> 00:00:41.541
- What's your day rate. chief?
- Whatever you're paying.

17
00:00:41.610 --> 00:00:43.851
Let's scoot.
[yells]

18
00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:44.955
- [growls]
- I named her Xena.

19
00:00:45.024 --> 00:00:47.886
after the Warrior Princess.

20
00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:49.920
Someone at the 10-Petal

21
00:00:49.989 --> 00:00:51.506
<i>knows more than they're saying.</i>

22
00:00:51.575 --> 00:00:53.300
[Wade] <i>That's a pretty
serious accusation.</i>

23
00:00:53.368 --> 00:00:54.782
[Whitney] <i>Yeah. well.
so is disappearing a man.</i>

24
00:00:54.886 --> 00:00:56.334
Let me take over.
Let me do the job for you.

25
00:00:56.403 --> 00:00:59.920
I wish I could. Kino.
Wish I could.

26
00:01:01.093 --> 00:01:03.403
- You sold me a sick bull.
- [yelling]

27
00:01:03.472 --> 00:01:05.334
You got 30 seconds to get
the fuck out of Rio Paloma.

28
00:01:05.403 --> 00:01:08.610
<i>and if I ever fucking see
your face again. you're dead.</i>

29
00:01:12.679 --> 00:01:15.472
♪ slow. somber music ♪

30
00:01:26.541 --> 00:01:28.679
[Rip]
Sure is quiet. isn't it?

31
00:01:29.851 --> 00:01:32.679
It ain't a ranch
without a herd. sweetheart.

32
00:01:34.886 --> 00:01:37.920
We'll fill these pastures
again one day.

33
00:01:38.679 --> 00:01:41.610
Might just take us a minute.
that's all.

34
00:01:43.506 --> 00:01:44.817
Yeah.

35
00:01:49.403 --> 00:01:52.300
Carter still hasn't
spoken to me.

36
00:01:53.989 --> 00:01:55.989
I should have told him.

37
00:01:57.472 --> 00:02:00.644
You ought to just give him
some time. He'll come around.

38
00:02:03.713 --> 00:02:05.162
You sure about this?

39
00:02:07.162 --> 00:02:10.403
Honey. it'll pay the bills
and put food on the table.

40
00:02:12.334 --> 00:02:13.955
Till we come up with a plan.

41
00:02:15.713 --> 00:02:17.713
We'll come up with a plan.

42
00:02:20.955 --> 00:02:23.058
- I love you.
- Love you.

43
00:02:34.817 --> 00:02:36.368
All right.

44
00:02:37.610 --> 00:02:40.541
♪

45
00:02:50.300 --> 00:02:51.713
<i>♪ Step right up ♪</i>

46
00:02:51.817 --> 00:02:53.196
["The Grand Tour"
by George Jones playing]

47
00:02:53.300 --> 00:02:55.886
[singing along]
<i>♪ Come on in ♪</i>

48
00:02:55.989 --> 00:02:57.955
<i>♪ If you'd like ♪</i>

49
00:02:58.024 --> 00:03:01.334
<i>♪ To take the grand tour ♪</i>

50
00:03:01.403 --> 00:03:04.610
<i>♪ Of a lonely house ♪</i>

51
00:03:04.713 --> 00:03:09.127
<i>♪ That once was
home sweet home...♪</i>

52
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:11.989
That's Beulah's son Joaquin.

53
00:03:12.058 --> 00:03:16.024
None of them are easy.
but he's reasonable.

54
00:03:16.093 --> 00:03:18.437
[panting]

55
00:03:20.748 --> 00:03:23.575
Morning. Joaquin.

56
00:03:23.610 --> 00:03:25.368
This is Rip Wheeler.

57
00:03:25.437 --> 00:03:27.713
Beulah wants to meet him.

58
00:03:27.748 --> 00:03:29.093
She expecting you?

59
00:03:29.196 --> 00:03:30.610
We didn't fix a time.

60
00:03:30.713 --> 00:03:32.955
but I ain't ever caught
your mother off guard.

61
00:03:33.782 --> 00:03:36.506
Huh. Come on in.

62
00:03:39.851 --> 00:03:42.920
[Everett]
Never ceases to amaze. the...

63
00:03:42.955 --> 00:03:45.989
the shit wealthy waste
their wealth on.

64
00:03:46.058 --> 00:03:47.575
Yeah.

65
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:50.955
She wants to speak
with you. Alone.

66
00:03:51.024 --> 00:03:52.162
Okay.

67
00:03:52.231 --> 00:03:53.817
Godspeed.
I'll wait for you in the truck.

68
00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:02.679
[exhales heavily]

69
00:04:06.886 --> 00:04:10.437
[sighs] I don't normally
take meetings at this hour.

70
00:04:10.506 --> 00:04:13.817
Well. Everett mentioned that
I might be able to help you.

71
00:04:13.920 --> 00:04:15.679
Oh.

72
00:04:17.851 --> 00:04:21.334
Uh. I hear you managed
the Yellowstone.

73
00:04:21.437 --> 00:04:23.300
Yes. ma'am. 25 years.

74
00:04:23.368 --> 00:04:24.610
Uh-huh. Then you bought

75
00:04:24.679 --> 00:04:26.437
the Edwards Ranch
with the Dutton girl?

76
00:04:26.506 --> 00:04:28.541
- My wife Beth. Yeah.
- Ah.

77
00:04:28.610 --> 00:04:30.196
It's good land.
it's better cattle.

78
00:04:30.265 --> 00:04:32.644
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

79
00:04:36.093 --> 00:04:38.575
You ever foreman'd
two properties?

80
00:04:38.644 --> 00:04:40.610
All due respect. ma'am.
your ranch

81
00:04:40.679 --> 00:04:42.093
and my ranch put together

82
00:04:42.162 --> 00:04:44.713
ain't a quarter
of what the Yellowstone is.

83
00:04:44.817 --> 00:04:46.162
So. you're a man
with an appetite.

84
00:04:46.196 --> 00:04:48.575
Nah. I'm just a man
that likes to work.

85
00:04:48.644 --> 00:04:50.437
Well. that's
an attractive quality.

86
00:04:50.506 --> 00:04:51.955
[chuckles]

87
00:04:52.024 --> 00:04:55.334
If you don't mind me asking.
who is. uh. Rob-Will?

88
00:04:55.403 --> 00:04:57.817
My son. Y'all have met?

89
00:04:57.886 --> 00:04:59.403
Briefly. yeah. Yeah.

90
00:04:59.472 --> 00:05:02.782
Well. let's just say
he's on an indefinite vacation.

91
00:05:02.886 --> 00:05:04.610
What else did Everett tell you?

92
00:05:04.679 --> 00:05:08.196
- Which part?
- About me needing help.

93
00:05:08.231 --> 00:05:09.472
Oh. uh...

94
00:05:09.541 --> 00:05:11.093
He mentioned that
your current foreman--

95
00:05:11.196 --> 00:05:13.782
these are his words. of course--
"is a fucking idiot."

96
00:05:13.851 --> 00:05:15.955
[laughs]

97
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:18.886
Ah. McKinney. He doesn't
pull punches. does he?

98
00:05:18.955 --> 00:05:20.955
No. ma'am. he doesn't.

99
00:05:22.679 --> 00:05:24.610
[sighs]
Well...

100
00:05:26.437 --> 00:05:28.024
...we got 75.000 acres.

101
00:05:28.093 --> 00:05:32.368
about 2.200 head.
Mexican crossbreed.

102
00:05:32.403 --> 00:05:34.920
We sell to big-box retailers.
but...

103
00:05:35.024 --> 00:05:37.782
mismanagement has been
a bit of a bugaboo of late.

104
00:05:37.851 --> 00:05:40.575
Well. would you like me
to fix your problem?

105
00:05:40.679 --> 00:05:42.058
Well. I wonder. can you?

106
00:05:42.093 --> 00:05:43.368
If it's ranching. I can.
Yes. ma'am.

107
00:05:43.403 --> 00:05:45.920
My margins have grown
razor-thin.

108
00:05:45.989 --> 00:05:49.265
I need someone
who implements efficiency.

109
00:05:49.368 --> 00:05:51.541
A man who works smarter.
not just harder.

110
00:05:51.575 --> 00:05:54.127
Well. I can do both.

111
00:05:54.196 --> 00:05:56.506
I like a tight-lipped ship.

112
00:05:56.575 --> 00:05:58.886
Rio Paloma loves to gossip.

113
00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:03.058
Well. ma'am. other people's
business. it ain't mine.

114
00:06:05.506 --> 00:06:08.265
Well. few names are
as revered as John Dutton's.

115
00:06:08.300 --> 00:06:11.162
I suppose if you worked
for him for 25 years.

116
00:06:11.231 --> 00:06:13.472
- you can work for anyone.
- Hmm.

117
00:06:15.265 --> 00:06:18.575
I also know that.
despite its tragic end.

118
00:06:18.644 --> 00:06:20.920
the Yellowstone was not
a three-ring circus.

119
00:06:20.989 --> 00:06:22.334
♪ slow. somber music ♪

120
00:06:22.437 --> 00:06:24.679
No. I wouldn't allow it.

121
00:06:25.644 --> 00:06:27.541
Do whatever it takes
to get my ranch in order.

122
00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:29.265
and I'll pay you handsomely.

123
00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:32.886
not just with my money
but with my loyalty.

124
00:06:32.955 --> 00:06:34.679
Hmm.

125
00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:38.989
I'll be here at 4:30 a.m.

126
00:06:39.093 --> 00:06:40.920
Pleasure to meet you.
Ms. Jackson.

127
00:06:40.955 --> 00:06:42.886
♪

128
00:06:43.748 --> 00:06:45.886
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

129
00:07:08.162 --> 00:07:11.265
♪

130
00:07:35.196 --> 00:07:37.368
♪

131
00:07:52.162 --> 00:07:54.368
- [wood creaks]
- [Rip sighs]

132
00:07:55.748 --> 00:07:58.368
You know this isn't
our only option.

133
00:07:59.231 --> 00:08:00.989
I could make some calls.

134
00:08:01.782 --> 00:08:03.610
Dallas. New York.

135
00:08:03.644 --> 00:08:06.058
I could be earning
within a month.

136
00:08:06.886 --> 00:08:09.334
But I'd be gone.

137
00:08:10.231 --> 00:08:12.334
No.

138
00:08:13.817 --> 00:08:15.886
I don't want that. darling.

139
00:08:17.575 --> 00:08:19.610
I want you next to me.

140
00:08:20.472 --> 00:08:22.437
Well. I'm always next to you.

141
00:08:22.472 --> 00:08:24.851
♪ gentle music

142
00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:26.610
I'll see you in a bit. sweetie.

143
00:08:40.575 --> 00:08:42.679
♪

144
00:09:02.506 --> 00:09:04.851
♪

145
00:09:21.713 --> 00:09:24.575
♪ dramatic. soaring music

146
00:09:46.541 --> 00:09:48.713
♪

147
00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:08.437
♪

148
00:10:26.541 --> 00:10:28.713
♪

149
00:10:33.196 --> 00:10:35.437
[TV playing indistinctly]

150
00:10:40.162 --> 00:10:41.679
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

151
00:10:41.748 --> 00:10:43.713
["Ain't That Right"
by Charley Crockett playing]

152
00:10:43.817 --> 00:10:46.231
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

153
00:10:47.058 --> 00:10:49.300
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

154
00:10:51.265 --> 00:10:53.610
<i>♪ We were up above it all ♪</i>

155
00:10:53.679 --> 00:10:56.679
<i>♪ Flying in your plane ♪</i>

156
00:10:56.748 --> 00:11:00.058
<i>♪ About the time
I had a bloody Mary ♪</i>

157
00:11:00.127 --> 00:11:03.748
<i>♪ Lord. I wasn't
feeling anything ♪</i>

158
00:11:03.782 --> 00:11:06.058
<i>♪ There you was
in all that leather ♪</i>

159
00:11:06.127 --> 00:11:09.437
<i>♪ With something on your mind ♪</i>

160
00:11:09.472 --> 00:11:12.437
<i>♪ I found out just what it was ♪</i>

161
00:11:12.506 --> 00:11:15.162
<i>♪ In the Salt Lake City lights ♪</i>

162
00:11:15.265 --> 00:11:17.575
- <i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>
- [coffee pouring]

163
00:11:17.679 --> 00:11:18.817
Who is that?

164
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:20.368
<i>♪ Ain't that right? ♪</i>

165
00:11:20.437 --> 00:11:21.610
Yeah. who the fuck are you?

166
00:11:21.644 --> 00:11:24.024
<i>♪ Ain't that right... ♪</i>

167
00:11:24.093 --> 00:11:26.093
We got calves to wean.

168
00:11:27.886 --> 00:11:29.989
Get your gear together

169
00:11:30.058 --> 00:11:32.506
and get your asses
in the saddle.

170
00:11:33.644 --> 00:11:36.300
Y'all got ten minutes.

171
00:11:38.334 --> 00:11:39.713
[music stops]

172
00:11:40.506 --> 00:11:43.196
Wait. I know you.
From the gas station.

173
00:11:43.265 --> 00:11:45.437
♪ exciting music ♪

174
00:11:53.782 --> 00:11:56.127
This is fucking bullshit.

175
00:12:07.024 --> 00:12:09.231
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

176
00:12:15.368 --> 00:12:17.093
- [Zach] Ma'am?
- Yeah?

177
00:12:17.162 --> 00:12:19.334
Horses are cared for.

178
00:12:19.368 --> 00:12:20.644
Anything else I can do?

179
00:12:20.679 --> 00:12:23.886
You can stop calling me "ma'am."

180
00:12:24.817 --> 00:12:27.093
- I've got a name.
- Oh. okay.

181
00:12:27.162 --> 00:12:30.231
Just know
that no work's beneath me.

182
00:12:37.368 --> 00:12:39.679
- He'd have liked you.
- Who?

183
00:12:40.575 --> 00:12:41.886
My dad.

184
00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:45.541
Sure would've liked
to have met him.

185
00:12:57.093 --> 00:12:58.713
Want one?

186
00:12:59.575 --> 00:13:01.024
Got one.

187
00:13:08.713 --> 00:13:11.334
Not much of a ranch anymore.

188
00:13:14.851 --> 00:13:16.403
Thank you.

189
00:13:19.886 --> 00:13:21.782
I keep looking for the herd.

190
00:13:23.541 --> 00:13:25.886
You know.
like they're still here.

191
00:13:26.713 --> 00:13:29.300
Take away something
you see every day...

192
00:13:30.162 --> 00:13:33.713
...sun. birds.

193
00:13:33.782 --> 00:13:35.610
wind even...

194
00:13:37.575 --> 00:13:40.024
...brain can't quite catch up.

195
00:13:44.472 --> 00:13:46.541
Was it 15 years you were inside?

196
00:13:48.368 --> 00:13:50.231
It's a long fucking time.

197
00:13:52.575 --> 00:13:54.713
What'd you miss the most?

198
00:13:54.817 --> 00:13:56.989
Lots of things.

199
00:13:59.265 --> 00:14:02.748
But mostly. the peace and quiet
of a lonely night.

200
00:14:04.575 --> 00:14:06.162
Yeah. I'd miss that.

201
00:14:06.955 --> 00:14:10.610
Not sure I'm meant
for peace. though.

202
00:14:12.713 --> 00:14:14.644
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

203
00:14:14.748 --> 00:14:16.506
Me. neither.

204
00:14:19.403 --> 00:14:23.127
But they say
God's ways are mysterious.

205
00:14:23.989 --> 00:14:25.713
Yeah.

206
00:14:25.782 --> 00:14:27.403
Mystery's right out there.

207
00:14:28.231 --> 00:14:30.437
For me. anyway.

208
00:14:31.334 --> 00:14:32.851
Right here.

209
00:14:35.472 --> 00:14:37.955
Land's as good a God as any.

210
00:14:39.300 --> 00:14:41.265
Maybe better.

211
00:14:45.920 --> 00:14:48.093
We keep looking. then.

212
00:14:48.955 --> 00:14:51.300
Keep trying. that's for sure.

213
00:14:56.231 --> 00:14:58.955
Hey. whatever you're working on
over there. Beth...

214
00:15:01.782 --> 00:15:03.748
...I hope it works.

215
00:15:03.817 --> 00:15:06.024
It fucking better.

216
00:15:13.782 --> 00:15:15.644
♪ fast. exciting music ♪

217
00:15:15.713 --> 00:15:17.817
[Rip]
Go on. start turning them out.

218
00:15:17.886 --> 00:15:19.024
[cattle lowing]

219
00:15:19.093 --> 00:15:21.713
[shouting. whistling]

220
00:15:21.782 --> 00:15:24.162
- Hey!
- Hey!

221
00:15:24.231 --> 00:15:25.300
Hey!

222
00:15:25.368 --> 00:15:28.368
[shouting. whistling]

223
00:15:31.541 --> 00:15:33.817
[shouting]

224
00:15:33.851 --> 00:15:35.300
[whistles]

225
00:15:35.368 --> 00:15:37.679
Go. keep turning them back.
let's go!

226
00:15:37.748 --> 00:15:39.541
- [whistles]
- Come on. Come on!

227
00:15:39.644 --> 00:15:41.334
Out of my way.

228
00:15:50.403 --> 00:15:53.575
[indistinct shouting]

229
00:15:53.679 --> 00:15:55.679
- [whistles]
- Find the gate. [grunts]

230
00:15:55.748 --> 00:15:57.679
- Hey!
- [shushing]

231
00:15:57.748 --> 00:15:59.506
Hey.

232
00:16:03.575 --> 00:16:05.265
- [whistling]
- Fucking son of a bitch

233
00:16:05.334 --> 00:16:07.300
doesn't know what spiderweb
he just walked into.

234
00:16:07.403 --> 00:16:09.610
Man. it was past time
to wean these calves.

235
00:16:09.679 --> 00:16:10.955
Fuck. Tommy. you think

236
00:16:11.058 --> 00:16:12.437
- I didn't know that?
- Quit fucking talking

237
00:16:12.541 --> 00:16:14.024
and go get them pairs.

238
00:16:14.093 --> 00:16:15.541
[Tommy]
Ah. yes. sir.

239
00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:17.024
[whooping]

240
00:16:17.851 --> 00:16:19.748
[Chet grunts]

241
00:16:19.817 --> 00:16:21.955
Hey!

242
00:16:26.162 --> 00:16:27.610
[cattle lowing]

243
00:16:33.989 --> 00:16:35.575
[vehicle approaching]

244
00:16:57.437 --> 00:16:59.058
[truck door opens]

245
00:17:03.748 --> 00:17:06.162
♪ slow. gentle music ♪

246
00:17:07.713 --> 00:17:10.541
[metal clanking]

247
00:17:12.575 --> 00:17:14.851
[creaking]

248
00:17:14.886 --> 00:17:16.610
Thought you could use
a little pick-me-up.

249
00:17:16.679 --> 00:17:18.437
It's not too soon?

250
00:17:18.506 --> 00:17:21.886
Nah. Some days.
too soon's all we got.

251
00:17:23.679 --> 00:17:26.231
Okay. girl. There you go.

252
00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:27.782
[clicking tongue]

253
00:17:27.851 --> 00:17:30.541
- How is she?
- She's doing great.

254
00:17:30.610 --> 00:17:34.644
You know. like you said.
this girl's got spirit.

255
00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:36.506
You got it. you got it.
There you go.

256
00:17:37.437 --> 00:17:39.162
Oh.

257
00:17:39.231 --> 00:17:41.334
There you go. Good job.

258
00:17:41.403 --> 00:17:43.886
Good girl. Good girl.

